commit.message: Remove remaining OMake stuff and ignore OCaml warnings
add cram system tests (exportdef test fails)
add cram tests and promote for linker_tests
update compiler_tests to use cram with dune

Change how we check if a file is writable

Since dune created artifacts are created without write permission, a
generated file may try to rewrite files that already exist and be denied
permission to do so. Instead of checking for permission denied
explicitly, check to see if the file already exists.

In either case, when a generated file is changed, the entire build
should be rebuilt to ensure the newest versions are present throughout
the build.
Only compile the `include` lib if on MacOS
fix dependencies in build so that it works the first time
